article.description: LIU Brooklyn holds on to beat St. Peter's 87-80
article.headline: LIU Brooklyn holds on to beat St. Peter's 87-80
article.linkText: LIU Brooklyn holds on to beat St. Peter's 87-80
article.story: BROOKLYN, N.Y. -- Gerrell Martin scored 24 points and made six 3-pointers to lead LIU Brooklyn past St. Peter's 87-80 on Saturday in a season opener for both teams. Jason Brickman added 13 points and dished out 14 assists. Brickman led all Division I players in assists last season with 290. He now needs 267 assists to become the fourth player in NCAA history to have 1,000 assists. Gilbert Parga made back-to-back 3-pointers to extend LIU's lead to 56-46 with 12:33 left. But St. Peter's clawed its way back and took its first lead of the second half at 69-68. Two LIU 3-pointers, during a 13-3 run, pushed the Blackbirds to an 81-72 lead with 49 seconds remaining. Marvin Dominique recorded a double-double with 31 points and 14 rebounds for St. Peter's. It was the 35th meeting all-time between the schools and the home team has now won the last seven contests.
